# Deskapp Changelog

---

## 0.8.0 — Proposal 08 — DataStore — 053126
Agent: Claude Sonnet 4.6

Added a persistent, thread-safe SQLite core layer available to every mod
as self.app.store. Database lives at ~/.config/deskapp/app.db; parent
directory is created automatically. Falls back to a no-op mode if the
file cannot be opened so the rest of the app continues.

New file: deskapp/src/store.py — DataStore class with full API:
ensure_table, execute, executemany, fetch, fetchone, table_exists, close.
One sqlite3.Connection (check_same_thread=False) guarded by a single
threading.Lock. sqlite3.Row row factory so all results are subscriptable
by column name.

deskapp/src/app.py — added import pathlib, DataStore import, self.store
init in App.__init__, and self.store.close() in App.close().

examples/ex_store.py — standalone StoreDemo module that exercises the
full lifecycle: ensure_table, executemany (seed), fetch (list render),
execute (insert/delete), fetchone (row count). Tab+Enter adds a note, D
deletes the selected row, status bar reflects store health.

---

## 0.7.0 — Proposal 07 — APT Pass 2 — 053126
Agent: Claude Sonnet 4.6

Second pass on deskapp/mods/apt.py (1039 lines). Three areas:

Patient workers: AptWorker.Kill() now escalates SIGTERM → wait(2s) →
SIGKILL. AptWorker.work() calls Process.kill() immediately on should_stop
rather than waiting for the read loop to drain. PackageListWorker and
UpgradableWorker check should_stop after the expensive Cache.open() call
and before emitting results. OnCmdLine auto-scroll now only fires when the
user is already near the bottom of the log — manual scroll position is
preserved while a command runs.

Floating log panel: LOG view now uses the backend's PageFloat / floating
panel infrastructure. RunShellAction and the L key call _EnableFloat(),
which sizes and enables the backend float panel. GoBack calls _DisableFloat().
page() in LOG view renders the previous view as a background; PageFloat()
draws the log as an overlay on top via the backend z-order system.

Structured detail view: apt show output is accumulated in RawDetailLines.
OnDetailDone parses it via ParseAptShow() (RFC 822 field parser with
continuation-line and blank-marker support) then builds formatted display
lines via BuildDetailLines(). Layout: Package/Version header, two-column
Arch+Size and Section+Priority rows, full-width Maintainer and Homepage,
unicode separator, word-wrapped Depends/Recommends/Suggests comma lists,
word-wrapped Description paragraphs. RenderDetail colors field headers cyan,
section headers yellow, separator blue, and content white.

---

## 0.6.0 — Proposal 06 — APT Module Rewrite — 053126
Agent: Claude Sonnet 4.6

Full rewrite of deskapp/mods/apt.py. Old scaffolding replaced with a
view-based modal TUI (ACTIONS / LIST / DETAIL / LOG views). New workers:
AptWorker (subprocess with Kill()), PackageListWorker (installed packages
via python-apt or dpkg fallback), UpgradableWorker (upgradable packages via
python-apt or apt list fallback). APT module now supports browsing installed
and upgradable packages, text-filter search, package detail (apt show),
install/remove/autoremove/upgrade with Y/N confirmation overlay, live log
view with manual scroll, and worker cancellation via C key. All blocking
apt calls moved to worker threads. 12 key callbacks registered.
Version held at 0.5.0 pending user confirmation.

---

## 0.5.0 — Proposal 05 — README Rewrite — 053126
Agent: Claude Sonnet 4.6

README replaced in full. Removed inaccurate content: nonexistent CLI entry
points (sidedesk, deskchat, deskapp-aws), multiplayer server claims that have
no source implementation, Windows platform support (POSIX only), dead links to
CONTRIBUTING.md and SECURITY.md. Removed fluff: 13-badge wall, time-estimate
tutorial blurb, game roadmap list, 2022 historic changelog block, broken
markdown code fence. Replaced with accurate description of what the framework
actually is, correct single entry point (deskapp), working quickstart, and
accurate Core API surface.
